  "texts": [
    "(111)Let ρ (2) and ρ ′(2) be the following irreducible 2-representationsρ (2) = (H L, [σ]), ρ ′(2) = (H L ′, [σ ′]).",
    "(112)Consider a local operator O changing L to L ′.",
    "The subgroupH L L ′:= H L ∩ H L ′ ⊆ G (0), (113)maps O to other local operators changing L to L ′.",
    "However, this action of H L L ′ is not linear, and instead satisfiesh 2 • (h 1 • O) = σ(h 2, h 1) σ ′ (h 2, h 1) (h 2 h 1) • O, ∀ h 1, h 2 ∈ H L L ′, (114)as explained in figure 14.Because of the factor σσ ′-1 (h 2, h 1) ∈ ×, non-genuine 0-charges from genuine 1-charge ρ (2) to genuine 1-charge ρ ′ (2) are not linear representations of H L L ′ in general.",
    "Such nongenuine 0-charges are linear representations only if[σσ ′-1]:= [σ H L L ′][σ ′ H L L ′] -1 = 1 ∈ H 2 (H L L ′, ×), (115)where[σ H L L ′] and [σ ′ H L L ′] are the restrictions of [σ] and [σ ′] to H L L ′, and 1 ∈ H 2 (H L L ′, ×) is the identity element."
